Steps to clone only branch Android for Android project

Step 1: get source from git repository
mkdir Flowchart.Android && cd Flowchart.Android
git init
git remote add origin git@github.com:tesera/Flowchart.git
vi .git/config, modify
fetch = +refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/origin/*
as
fetch = +refs/heads/Android:refs/remotes/origin/Android
git pull origin

Step 2: create eclipse project from existing source
1. Choose menu: File - New - Project
2. Select project type: Android - Android Project, then click Next
3. Fill "Project name": Flowchart,
   Check "Create project from existing source",
   Select the "Location" where Flowchart.Android locates,
   Make sure "Build Target" is selectable and select something like "Android 2.2", etc,
   Make sure "Properties" automatically recognized as "FlowchartActivity", "com.explorus.flowchart", etc
   Click "Finish"


